description:
Japanese title: Bakuhatsu! Sennin Mōdo (爆発! 仙人モード)

Sensing danger at hand, Naruto, along with Fukasaku, rushes back to the Leaf Village from Mount Myoboku. But what they see is the remains of the Leaf Village, leveled beyond recognition.
name: Explosion! Sage Mode

description:
Japanese title: Pinchi! Kieta Sennin Mōdo (危機! 消えた仙人モード)

Naruto hits Pain with his Sage Jutsu-perfected Wind Style Rasen Shuriken. Although he succeeds in defeating Ningendo, the remaining Pain quickly confronts him.
name: Danger! Sage Mode Limit Reached

description:
Japanese title: Kyūbi Hokaku Kanryō (九尾捕獲完了)

Gamabunta and the other toads are defeated while Naruto is captured by Pain. Naruto attempts to fight back with Sage Jutsu, but Gakido sucks out his chakra, forcing him to go out of Sage Mode.
name: Nine Tails, Captured!

description:
Japanese title: Kokuhaku (告白)

Fukasaku and Shima fall in battle, leaving Naruto open to be captured by Tendo Pain. Just when all is thought to be lost, Hinata, who was following the battle with her Byakugan, steps in to face Pain.
name: Confessions

description:
Japanese title: Chibaku Tensei (地爆天星)

Naruto loses himself after seeing Hinata taken out right before his eyes. His anger triggers the Nine Tails’ chakra to go out of control.
name: Planetary Devastation

description:
Japanese title: Yondaime Hokage (四代目火影)

Naruto meets Minato Namikaze, the Fourth Hokage, inside his inner world.
name: Fourth Hokage

description:
Japanese title: Futari no Deshi (ふたりの弟子)

To break the cycle of hate, Naruto heads to where the real Pain is hiding.
name: The Two Students

description:
Japanese title: Daibōken! Yondaime no Isan o Sagase - Zenpen (大冒険! 四代目の遺産を探せ・前編)

The story goes back to right before the start of the final rounds of the Chunin Exam. As Naruto trains in preparation for his upcoming match, he hears Jiraiya speak of “the Fourth Hokage’s legacy.”
name: Big Adventure! The Quest for the Fourth Hokage’s Legacy, Part 1

description:
Japanese title: Daibōken! Yondaime no Isan o Sagase - Kōhen (大冒険! 四代目の遺産を探せ・後編)

Naruto and the others take on the oncoming challenges in order to find the secret technique and break the previous record set by the Fourth Hokage.
name: Big Adventure! The Quest for the Fourth Hokage's Legacy - Part 2

description:
Japanese title: Deai (出逢い)

Naruto comes face to face with Nagato and Konan. Naruto, wanting to confront the problem of their hate-filled ninja world, asks to hear Nagato’s side of the story before coming up with an answer.
name: Meeting

description:
Japanese title: Pein Tanjō (ペイン誕生)

To fulfill their dream, Nagato, Yahiko, and Konan walk through the war zone in search of Jiraiya, hoping to learn ninjutsu from him.
name: Origin of Pain

first_appearance_objects.name: Demonic Statue of the Outer Path

object_credits.name: Demonic Statue of the Outer Path

description:
Japanese title: Uzumaki Naruto Monogatari (うずまきナルト物語)

Naruto remains silent after learning of Nagato’s painful past. Nagato claims true peace cannot exist in this cursed world, dismissing Jiraiya’s ideal as nothing more than wishful thinking.
name: Tale of Naruto Uzumaki

description:
Japanese title: Konoha no Eiyū (木ノ葉の英雄)

Nagato, having decided to believe in Naruto’s word, performs his last forbidden jutsu: Gedo Art Rinne Rebirth.
name: Hero of the Hidden Leaf

description:
Japanese title: Shinmai Kyōshi Iruka (新米教師イルカ)

The Leaf Village is left in ruins in the wake of Pain’s assault on the village. While cleaning through the remains of Ninja Academy, Iruka finds an old pillar and recognizes it as a memoir from Naruto’s early years at the academy.
name: Rookie Instructor Iruka

description:
Japanese title: Iruka no Shiren (イルカの試練)

Naruto spends his days competing with Sasuke, the academy’s star student, only to screw up and be the laughingstock of the class.
name: Iruka's Ordeal

description:
Japanese title: Iruka no Ketsui (イルカの決意)

Naruto takes up his classmates’ dare to venture into the forest and retrieve an item from dead enemy ninja, unaware that the forest is dangerous.
name: Iruka's Decision

first_appearance_objects.name: Demonic Statue of the Outer Path

object_credits.name: Demonic Statue of the Outer Path

description:
Japanese title: Tantō Jōnin Hatake Kakashi (担当上忍はたけカカシ)

An emergency council is held before the Feudal Lord of the Land of Fire. The topic is to discuss plans to rebuild the Leaf Village, and Danzo strongly urges the council to select a new Hokage to replace Tsunade.
name: Kakashi Hatake, The Jonin in Charge

description:
Japanese title: Inari, Tamesareru Yūki (イナリ、試される勇気)

The Leaf ninja work to rebuild the Hidden Leaf Village.
name: Inari's Courage Put to the Test

description:
Japanese title: Naruto, Adauchi Shinanjuku (ナルト、仇討ち指南塾)

Team 7 stops in a town for some rest, where they encounter a man named Tsukado who is out to avenge the death of his relative.
name: Naruto's School of Revenge

description:
Japanese title: Gaara 'Kizuna' (我愛羅『絆』)

Gaara, recalling a past mission carried out with the Leaf’s Team 7, points out that the Leaf Village has Naruto with them.
name: Gaara’s Bond

description:
Japanese title: Naruto Autobureiku (ナルト・アウトブレイク)

Naruto visits Sakura, who is caring for Tsunade. Sakura recalls an incident that took place three years before, in which she collapsed from symptoms that resembled a disease caused by a mysterious virus.
name: Naruto: Outbreak

description:
Japanese title: Shutsugeki! Tenten-han (出撃! テンテン班)

Tenten and Neji head for the Leaf Ninja Tool Research Lab to procure ninja tools necessary for rebuilding the Leaf Village.
name: Deploy! Team Tenten

description:
Japanese title: Animaru Bangaichi (アニマル番外地)

Condor, the ostrich previously captured by Team 7, now lives in a forest with baby ostriches. Since his last escape, Condor has trained himself to become a ninja ostrich.
name: Animal District

description:
Japanese title: Aa, Seishun no Kanpōgan (ああ、青春の漢方丸)

After accidentally finishing off Lee’s last special youth drink, Naruto asks Guy to make more, only to learn one of its key ingredients, the Jofuku Flower, is out of stock.
name: Ah, the Medicine of Youth

description:
Japanese title: Dokonjō Shitei Shugyōhen (ド根性師弟修業編)

Jiraiya takes Naruto to a village in the hopes of teaching him how to counter the Sharingan’s genjutsu attack.
name: Gutsy Master and Student: The Training

description:
Japanese title: Dokonjō Shitei Ninpūroku (ド根性師弟忍風録)

Naruto and Jiraiya attempt to save a village from Kandachi, a former right-hand man to Hanzo of the Hidden Rain.
name: Record of the Gutsy Ninja Master and Student

description:
Japanese title: Sasuke no Nikukyū Taizen (サスケの肉球大全)

Granny Cat requests that Sasuke and Team 7 collect the last cat paw print necessary to complete the “Paw Encyclopedia.”
name: Sasuke's Paw Encyclopedia

description:
Japanese title: Naruto to Rōhei (ナルトと老兵)

Naruto is assigned to a team led by jonin Hayama to patrol the north border of the Leaf Village. One of his teammates is Kosuke, an old man who has been a genin for over fifty years, earning him the title “Eternal Genin.”
name: Naruto and the Old Soldier

description: Peggy discovers the shocking truth about Leviathan but doesn't realize that her true enemies are even closer than she imagined. Meanwhile, Souza is close to confirming the truth about Peggy and may just put her in the crosshairs of the SSR.
name: A Sin to Err

description: Peggy is cornered and more vulnerable than ever as Leviathan makes their move against her. As the SSR zeroes in on Howard Stark, they may pay the ultimate price as they find their true enemy is closer than they realized
name: Snafu

description: Peggy faces the full fury of Leviathan, as Howard Stark makes his return in the explosive season finale.
name: Valediction

deck: In hopes of having new additions to his traveling circus, a ringmaster captures Sonic and his friends.
name: Circus of Plunders

deck: Tails reprograms one of Eggman's robots and accidentally turns it into a killing machine determined to destroy Eggman. Because it's their fault, Sonic and Tails must protect their enemy and move into Eggman's evil lair for a night of bonding.
name: Cowbot

deck: Orbot and Cubot wake up with no memory of the previous day's events. On top of that, Eggman is missing. The two bots set out to find Eggman by figuring out exactly what happened the day before.
name: Dude, Where's My Eggman?

deck: Millions of years after the mysterious and powerful Energems were entrusted to the now extinct dinosaurs for protection from a ruthless bounty hunter, a pair of courageous teens find themselves in possession of two of these long lost precious artifacts, and come face to face with a monster who will do everything in his power to steal them for himself.
name: Powers From the Past

deck: After all the recent trials the group has faced, a slight detour might prove to be the solution they've been looking for.
name: What Happened and What's Going On

has_staff_review.name: The Walking Dead Episode #509 - "What Happened and What's Going On"

description: The crew is forced to transport some unusual cargo when a gamble with a new acquaintance doesn't pay off.
name: Idiot's Array

description: The crew of the Ghost try to thwart an Imperial plan to capture an exiled dignitary who wants to host a secret rally on Lothal.
name: Vision of Hope

description: As public awareness increases around the Rebels' activity, they target an important Imperial network.
name: Call to Action

deck: Before Ash’s battle against Grant at the Cyllage City Gym, our heroes visit the Muraille Coast, the suspected site of a ship that sank long ago. Ash and Serena join an underwater archeologist in her submarine to look for the lost luxury liner. What they find is breathtaking to behold! Wild Water-type Pokémon have made the shipwreck into a home under the sea, and more recently, so has Team Rocket...
name: An Undersea Place to Call Home!

deck: Team Flash attempts to understand what's going on with Ronnie and how they can save him.
description: After Ronnie (guest-star Robbie Amell) attacks a physicist (guest-star Bill Dow), Barry (Grant Gustin) and the team realize they need to go after Caitlin's (Danielle Panabaker) fiance, who is now a dangerous meta-human. They deduce the best way to track Ronnie is to find Dr. Martin Stein (guest-star Victor Garber), who was working on a project called F.I.R.E.S.T.O.R.M. Barry struggles to balance his duties as The Flash and his relationship with Linda Park (guest-star Malese Jow), and Joe (Jesse L. Martin) enlists Cisco's (Carlos Valdes) help to reinvestigate the murder of Nora Allen (guest-star Michelle Harrison). General Eiling (Clancy Brown) returns to Central City.
name: The Nuclear Man
